aming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"4\"| [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| <ref name=\"Release\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| United States\n| September 3, 2019\n| [[Contemporary hit radio]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|publisher=All Access Media Group|accessdate=August 30, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830103325/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archivedate=August 30, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 16, 2019\n| [[Hot adult contemporary]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allaccess.com/hot-modern-ac/future-releases|title=Hot/Modern/AC Future Releases|publisher=All Access Media Group|accessdate=September 12, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190912154436/https://www.allaccess.com/hot-modern-ac/future-releases|archivedate=September 12, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| November 7, 2019\n| {{hlist|[[7-inch single]]||[[CD single]]|[[cassette single]]}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://shop.postmalone.com/products/circles-7-vinyl-digital-single?variant=31155433963604|title=\"Circles\" 7\" Vinyl Single + Digital Single|website=Post Malone {{!}} Official Shop|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191111025727/https://shop.postmalone.com/products/circles-7-vinyl-digital-single?variant=31155433963604|archivedate=November 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://shop.postmalone.com/products/circles-cd-digital-single?variant=31155440615508|title=\"Circles\" CD Single + Digital Single|website=Post Malone {{!}} Official Shop|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191111030617/https://shop.postmalone.com/products/circles-cd-digital-single?variant=31155440615508||archivedate=November 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://shop.postmalone.com/products/circles-cassette-digital-single?variant=31155442843732|title=\"Circles. Cassette Single + Digital Single|website=Post Malone {{!}} Official Shop|accessdate=November 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191112060843/https://shop.postmalone.com/products/circles-cassette-digital-single?variant=31155442843732|archivedate=November 12, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles of 2019|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 number-one singles of 2019]]\n* [[List of Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles of 2020|List of ''Billboard'' Hot 100 number-one singles of 2020]]\n* [[List of number-one songs of 2019 (Malaysia)]]\n* [[List of number-one singles from the 2010s (New Zealand)#2019|List of number-one singles from the 2010s (New Zealand)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Youtube|pQV0WEdT_OE|Audio}}\n*{{MetroLyrics song|post-malone|circles}}\n\n{{Post Malone}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:American pop rock songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Iceland]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in New Zealand]]\n[[Category:Post Malone songs]]\n[[Category:Republic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Frank Dukes]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Louis Bell]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Frank Dukes]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Louis Bell]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Post Malone]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Circles\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Post Malone - Circles.png\n| alt        =\n| artist     = [[Post Malone]]\n| album      = [[Hollywood's Bleeding]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|08|30|mf=y}}\n| recorded   = <!-- Please source recording dates/years -->{{start date|2018|08|08|mf=y}}<!-- source can be found in lawsuit section -->\n| studio     =\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Single (music)#7-inch format|7\"]]|[[Cassette single|cassette]]|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| genre      = <!-- DO NOT change without source -->[[Pop rock]]<!-- source can be found in composition section -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=34}}\n| label      = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Post Malone|Austin Post]]|[[Frank Dukes|Adam Feeney]]|Billy Walsh|Miles Ale|[[Louis Bell]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Post Malone|[[Frank Dukes]]|Bell}}\n| prev_title =    [[Goodbyes (Post Malone song)|Goodbyes]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title =                  \n  [[Enemies (Post Malone song)|Enemies]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|wXhTHyIgQ_U|\"Circles\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Circles'''\" is a song by American rapper and singer [[Post Malone]], released through [[Republic Records]] on August 30, 2019,<ref name=\"Release\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8528658/post-malone-circles-single-release-date|title=Post Malone Announces 'Circles' Single Release Date|work=Billboard|last=Aniftos|first=Rania|date=August 28, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> as the third single from Malone's third studio album ''[[Hollywood's Bleeding]]'' (2019).<ref name=\"AP\"/> It reached number one on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] for the week of November 30, 2019, topping the chart for three non-consecutive weeks,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8547374/post-malone-circles-hot-100-number-one-third-week|title=Post Malone 'Circles' Back to No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Maroon 5 & Roddy Ricch Reach Top Three|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=January 6, 2019|accessdate=January 6, 2019}}</ref> marking Post Malone's fourth number-one song, as well as his first solo effort to chart at number-one.<ref name=\"Number One\"/> The single is as of February 2020 the first and only song by a solo male artist (no features) to achieve double-digit frames at number one on the ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Top 40|Pop Songs]] chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2020/02/18/post-malone-makes-history-on-the-pop-songs-chart/#3684f5a76ce9|title=Post Malone Makes History On The Pop Songs Chart|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|date=February 18, 2020|website=[[Forbes (magazine)|Forbes]]||accessdate=February 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nPost Malone premiered the song live during his Bud Light Dive Bar Tour show in [[New York City]] on August 5, where he claimed it would be released the following week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/post-malone-circles-new-album-release-date/|title=Post Malone Performs A New Song Called 'Circles' And Shares Details About His Next Album|website=[[Uproxx]]|last=Rossignol|first=Derrick|date=August 6, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> A snippet of the track was posted to Malone's [[YouTube]] channel the same day.<ref name=\"AP\">{{cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/post-malone-circles-release-date/|title=Post Malone confirms \"Circles\" release date following previous live debut|work=[[Alternative Press (magazine)|Alternative Press]]|last=Shoemaker|first=Whitney|date=August 28, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> He previewed the song in August 2019 on ''[[the Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/post-malone-drops-new-song-circles-listen/|title=Post Malone Drops New Song Circles|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=August 30, 2019|accessdate=August 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n\"Circles\" is a [[pop rock]] song consisting of a \"bouncy, [[Sadness|melancholy]]\" melody, alongside a \"gentle [[Acoustic music|acoustic]] [[Groove (music)|groove]]\". The chorus has been described as \"compulsory [[Sing-along|singalong]]\".<ref name=\"Billboard Bo2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/8545893/best-songs-of-2019-top-100|title=The 100 Best Songs of 2019: Staff List|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|author=''Billboard'' staff|date=December 11, 2019|accessdate=December 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' described the song as being \"backed by sunny acoustic guitars, swirling percussion and infectious melodies\",<ref name=\"Live debut\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8526255/post-malone-bud-light-dive-bar-tour-show-recap|title=Post Malone Debuts New Song 'Circles,' Shares New Album Details at Intimate Bud Light Concert|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Spruch|first=Kirsten|date=August 6, 2019|accessdate=August 29, 2019}}</ref> and that while it has a \"funky feel, the meaning is a bit more somber, detailing a relationship gone cold\".<ref name=\"Release\"/>\n\nIt was named the seventh best song of 2019 by ''Billboard.''<ref name=\"Billboard Bo2\"/>\n\n==Chart performance==\nOn the chart dated November 30, 2019, \"Circles\" became Post Malone's fourth number one on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and his first as the only credited artist on a track.<ref name=\"Number One\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8544750/post-malone-circles-number-one-hot-100|title=Post Malone's 'Circles' Hits No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Billie Eilish's 'Everything I Wanted' Blasts to Top 10|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 25, 2019}}</ref> It also marked his second Hot 100 number one of 2019, following \"[[Sunflower (Post Malone and Swae Lee song)|Sunflower]]\" with [[Swae Lee]], which led the chart in January.<ref name=\"Number One\" /> Spending 33 weeks on the top 10 of the Hot 100, it tied [[Ed Sheeran]]'s \"[[Shape of You]]\" (2017), [[Maroon 5]] and [[Cardi B]]'s \"[[Girls Like You]]\" (2018) and Malone and [[Swae Lee]]'s \"[[Sunflower (Post Malone and Swae Lee song)|Sunflower]]\" (2019) as the singles that logged [[List of Billboard Hot 100 chart achievements and milestones#Most total weeks in the top 10|the most weeks in that region]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/9361802/weeknd-blinding-lights-three-weeks-number-one-hot-100|title=The Weeknd Returns to No. 1 on Billboard Hot 100, Doja Cat Hits Top 5, Post Malone Ties Top 10 Record|work=Billboard|last=Trust|first=Gary|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\nElsewhere, the song also peaked at number one in Iceland, Malaysia and New Zealand, number two in Canada, Australia, Ireland, Norway, Singapore and Slovakia, while reaching the top 3 in the UK and the top five in several other nations.\n\n==Lawsuit==\nMalone filed a lawsuit against songwriter Tyler Armes for \"falsely claiming that he is a co-author of the musical composition contained in the 'Circles' track\". He stated that although Armes was present when the track was recorded on August 8, 2018, he did not make contributions to the track.<ref name-\"page6\">{{cite web|url= https://pagesix.com/2020/04/07/post-malone-sues-over-circles/|title=Post Malone in legal battle over 'Circles'|website=[[Page Six]]|author=Chelsea Hirsch|date=April 7, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> According to the complaint from Malone, he continued to work with songwriters Walsh, Gunesberk and Bell in subsequent sessions after August 8, while Armes wasn't present in either of those sessions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/legal-and-management/9353540/post-malone-songwriter-circles-lawsuit|title=Post Malone & Songwriter File Dueling Lawsuits Over 'Circles' Credit|last=Rosenbaum|first=Claudia|date=April 7, 2020|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video, directed by [[Colin Tilley]], was released on September 3, 2019. Post plays a knight in armor who wanders across a war-torn rural countryside, watched through a magic mirror by a strange woman with no mouth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8528955/post-malone-circles-video|title=Post Malone Comes Back to Life in Bloodthirsty 'Circles' Video|work=Billboard|last=Saponara|first=Michael|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=September 4, 2019}}</ref> As of April 2020, the video has reached over 200 million views.\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/116483937|title=Circles / Post Malone|publisher=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|accessdate=September 13, 2019}}</ref>\n\n* [[Post Malone]] \u2013 principal vocalist, songwriting, producer, programming, guitar\n* [[Frank Dukes]] \u2013 production, programming, songwriting\n* [[Louis Bell]] \u2013 production, recording, vocal production, programming, songwriting\n* Miles Ale \u2013 guitar, songwriting\n* Billy Walsh \u2013 songwriting\n* [[Manny Marroquin]] \u2013 mixing\n* Chris Galland \u2013 mixing assistant\n* Robin Florent \u2013 mixing assistant\n* Scott Desmarais \u2013 mixing assistant\n* Jeremie Inhaber \u2013 mixing assistant\n* [[Mike Bozzi]] \u2013 mastering\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardargentinahot100|87|artist=Post Malone|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 22, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|2|artist=Post Malone|song=Circles|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 14, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|9|artist=Post Malone|song=Circles|rowheader=true|accessdate=September 22, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|5|artist=Post Malone|song=Circles|rowheader=true|accessdate=November 9, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|15|artist=Post Malone|song=Circles|rowheader=true|accessdate=December 7, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Brazil ([[Top 100 